      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>71</offset>
        <text>In large swaths of the ocean, primary production by diatoms may be limited by the availability of silica, which in turn limits the biological uptake of carbon dioxide.
</text>
        <annotation id="T17">
          <infon key="brat-id">T17</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="14" offset="223"/>
          <text>carbon dioxide</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T18">
          <infon key="brat-id">T18</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="6" offset="213"/>
          <text>uptake</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E10">
          <infon key="brat-id">E10</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T18" role="Increase"/>
          <node refid="T17" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>239</offset>
        <text>The burial of biogenic silica in the form of opal is the main sink of marine silicon.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>325</offset>
        <text>Opal burial occurs in equal parts in iron-limited open-ocean provinces and upwelling margins, especially the eastern Pacific upwelling zone.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>466</offset>
        <text>However, it is unclear why opal burial is so efficient in this margin.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>537</offset>
        <text>Here we measure fluxes of biogenic material, concentrations of diatom-bound iron and silicon isotope ratios using sediment traps and a sediment core from the Gulf of California upwelling margin.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>732</offset>
        <text>In the sediment trap material, we find that periods of intense upwelling are associated with transient iron limitation that results in a high export of silica relative to organic carbon.
</text>
        <annotation id="T3">
          <infon key="brat-id">T3</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="43" offset="874"/>
          <text>export of silica relative to organic carbon</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T4">
          <infon key="brat-id">T4</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="4" offset="869"/>
          <text>high</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E2">
          <infon key="brat-id">E2</infon>
